author: eTN Managing Editor
title: Many dead at Central Train Station terror attack in Ankara, Turkey
text:
Many dead at Central Train Station terror attack in Ankara, Turkey   10, 2015 eTN   
Tourists and local travelers arriving or leaving from Ankara's Central Railway station Saturday morning had a horrifying experience, when an alleged suicide bomber attacked outside the train station with two explosions at a road junction next to the train station. Ankara Central Railway station is the busiest in Turkey serving 181 trains daily. 
The explosion occurred during a demonstration for “labor, peace and democracy” that started at 10:00 local time (0700 GMT). 
According to Dogan news agency at least 20 people have been killed in the two explosions, dozens seriously wounded. This crime has been labeled a terrorist attack. These numbers of dead and injured are expected to go up. 
Turkey has a popular travel and tourism destination.
